				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Solve one problem at a time. First start with generating a simple square wave with your OS. Once you have that, generate one with a half-period specified in 1/1789773ths of a second. Once you have that, implement a basic NES APU that supports one square wave with frequency only, nothing else (that is, you only look at writes to $4002 and the low three bits of $4003). Once that plays the first channel of songs at the right pitch, you can start adding more stuff.</div>

